[SPEAKER_07]: Mr JJ.

236
00:25:28,432 --> 00:25:44,677
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you very much, you know, in terms of the practice the practices at the middle school level certainly that anytime there is a report of bullying all parties in their parents guardians caregivers would be would be contacted, you know, certainly we're going to be working with each one of the families in different contexts hand in hand.

237
00:25:45,530 --> 00:25:53,456
[SPEAKER_02]: in order to make sure they're apprised of a situation and, you know, understanding what the next steps are going to be while respecting confidentiality too as well.

238
00:25:54,197 --> 00:26:00,322
[SPEAKER_02]: So, you know, certainly, you know, if we want to denote perhaps on some sort of a sheet of paper.

239
00:26:01,402 --> 00:26:23,228
[SPEAKER_02]: to denote the contacts, the times at which we have gone ahead and made contact that might be helpful for documentation standpoints and also for families to understand that that's a level of service and care we're going to provide to them to make sure that we provide them with that level of understanding and transparency and communication throughout this process that's difficult for all parties involved.

240
00:26:26,269 --> 00:26:26,609
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

241
00:26:27,930 --> 00:26:28,370
[SPEAKER_07]: Mr. Downs?

