262
00:28:34,092 --> 00:28:39,513
[SPEAKER_02]: I also wanted to bring up a point that I think might be worthy of reflecting, perhaps, in this new document.

263
00:28:40,194 --> 00:28:55,277
[SPEAKER_02]: We've recently begun using the Sandy Hook Say Something reporting system, which I've found to be useful and helpful, certainly, to be able to give students and families another avenue to be able to document a concern.

264
00:28:55,297 --> 00:29:02,819
[SPEAKER_02]: It doesn't always have to be about bullying or cyberbullying, but oftentimes the reports that we're seeing coming in at the secondary level are of that sort.

265
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:13,927
[SPEAKER_02]: These are, you know, certainly we've trained our students to find trusted adults in our school community and our community in general to be able to, you know, tell these things to and have conversations about.

266
00:29:14,608 --> 00:29:28,479
[SPEAKER_02]: But there's this added layer now that we have where students can anonymously send these tips to school administrators like myself and there's a whole team of folks through Sandy Hook that will then stream it and then send it to the appropriate parties, a person like myself.

267
00:29:29,340 --> 00:29:38,227
[SPEAKER_02]: What I've found to be a little bit of a problem of practice is that sometimes we don't know who is sending this tip, obviously, because it's anonymous in nature.

268
00:29:39,028 --> 00:29:44,892
[SPEAKER_02]: And it is troublesome and difficult at times to be able to follow up.

269
00:29:45,673 --> 00:29:47,855
[SPEAKER_02]: But certainly, many of these tips are very, very useful.

270
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:50,617
[SPEAKER_02]: So I wanted to just at least put that out there.

271
00:29:50,977 --> 00:29:53,780
[SPEAKER_02]: Perhaps we can note the fact that we're using this anonymous tip line.

272
00:29:54,760 --> 00:30:08,618
[SPEAKER_02]: As another layer of support for our students and families, but also just note the fact that sometimes it does add an element of challenge for us to be able to follow up with this anonymous tipster to receive the appropriate information.

273
00:30:09,199 --> 00:30:10,721
[SPEAKER_02]: And sometimes we found that these tips we.

274
00:30:12,002 --> 00:30:27,498
[SPEAKER_02]: They may be even unfounded, you know where we may just be given a random tip about somebody, and we just don't have enough information, we try to do our best to engage, whoever the tipster might be in the moment, but, you know, we're still learning a little about this process we're working with Sandy hook about it.

275
00:30:28,138 --> 00:30:36,781
[SPEAKER_02]: But I think it may be worthy of mentioning in our bullying, you know, new bullying plan, the fact that we have this new system.

